VI  - 36
IP  - 2
DP  - 1975 Aug
TI  - Six families prone to ovarian cancer.
PG  - 364-9
AB  - Six families are presented with multiple cases of ovarian cancer, mainly serous 
      cystadenocarcinoma. Three families had concomitant aggregation of breast cancer, 
      suggesting genetic determinants common to both tumors. The exceptional cancer 
      risk in these families prompted prophylactic oophorectomy in 14 asymptomatic 
      women from four families. Review of the original microscopic sections from 8 
      women revealed that 3, representing two families, had abnormalities of ovarian 
      surface epithelium and mesothelial tissue, which may be of etiologic significance 
      and portend neoplastic changes. To enable early detection and prevention of 
      ovarian cancer, new diagnostic techniques and etiologic studies should be applied 
      whenever possible to high-risk families.
