TI  - [Malignant lymphopathy and breast cancer (apropos of 3 cases)].
PG  - 2781-9
AB  - Two cases of Hodgkin's disease were associated with a breast tumor after a 
      remission of seven years. Conversely, another patient was affected by a mammary 
      adenocarcinoma prior to the onset of an overt acute lymphoblastic leukemia in the 
      same delay. These three observations focussed our attention upon the development 
      of secondary neoplasias and the possible relationship between both types of 
      disorders. In a period with extensive research on cancer etiology, it seemed 
      interesting to discuss the role of several factors: genetic, therapeutic and/or 
      immunological ones.
